All clean. Summary of what was fixed in the transfer flow:


  handleTransfer (page.tsx)
  - if (wei > decryptedBalance) throw — prevents computing/submitting an overdraft that would wrap the EC point into an invalid ciphertext
  - try { BigInt(recipientPkX/Y) } catch — surfaces "Invalid recipient public key format" instead of a cryptic JS SyntaxError
  - await checkRegistered(rpkX, rpkY) before doing any crypto work — surfaces "Recipient is not registered on Veil" locally instead of paying gas for an        
  on-chain revert

  TransferModal
  - Receives balance: bigint, shows "Available: X.XXXX STRK" above the amount field
  - MAX button fills the input with the full balance
  - Client-side wei > balance check gives an instant error before even calling onSubmitAll clean. Summary of what was fixed in the transfer flow:

